 :tx/rationale "THREE-SESSION CONVERGENCE TEST: The only test that validates braid's core hypothesis — does the system learn across sessions? Protocol: Agent 1 starts cold (no concepts, no seed). Makes 10 observations on Go CLI. Harvests. Concepts crystallize from observations. Agent 2 seeds from Agent 1's harvest. Makes 10 more observations. The emergent concepts and frontier guide Agent 2. Agent 3 seeds from Agent 2's harvest. Makes 10 more observations. CONVERGENCE METRICS: (A) Surprise entropy — Agent 1 has uniform surprise (everything new), Agent 3 has concentrated surprise (only frontier is surprising). (B) Coverage rate — Agent 3 covers more unique ground per observation than Agent 1. (C) Discovery depth — Agent 3 finds architectural insights in observations 1-3 that Agent 1 didn't find until 8-10. (D) Silence ratio — the fraction of observations that get one-line confirms increases across sessions. (E) The qualitative gold standard: Agent 3 says 'I would not have found this without the seed.' Converging = braid learns. Flat = harvest/seed is broken. Diverging = system is harmful. Traces to: ADR-FOUNDATION-014, OBSERVER-4, OBSERVER-6, C7."
